comment:
* Defines error codes returned during SIP actions. For example, during
 * {@link SipRegistrationListener#onRegistrationFailed onRegistrationFailed()},
 * {@link SipSession.Listener#onError onError()},
 * {@link SipSession.Listener#onCallChangeFailed onCallChangeFailed()} and
 * {@link SipSession.Listener#onRegistrationFailed onRegistrationFailed()}.
 * @deprecated {@link android.net.sip.SipManager} and associated classes are no longer supported and
 * should not be used as the basis of future VOIP apps.

variables.name: SERVER_ERROR
variables.comment: When server responds with an error.

variables.name: CLIENT_ERROR
variables.comment: When some error occurs on the device, possibly due to a bug.

variables.name: TIME_OUT
variables.comment: When the transaction gets timed out.

variables.name: INVALID_REMOTE_URI
variables.comment: When the remote URI is not valid.

variables.name: PEER_NOT_REACHABLE
variables.comment: When the peer is not reachable.

variables.name: IN_PROGRESS
variables.comment: The client is in a transaction and cannot initiate a new one.

variables.name: SERVER_UNREACHABLE
variables.comment: When the server is not reachable.
